      "solution": "n = gets.to_i\n\n# Incorrect -- 147 is (4^2)*7 + (4^1)*7 + (4^0)*7, but base 4 doesn't have the symbol 7\n# b = (2..12000).find { |b| b*b*7 + b*7 + 7 }\n\n# Correct -- Start searching at base 8 instead of base 2\n# b = (8..12000).find { |b| b*b*7 + b*7 + 7 }\n\n# Incorrect -- 1869 is (77, 7) in base 256, but we want (7, 7, 7)\n# b = (2..12000).find { |b| n.digits(b).join == '777' }\n\n# Correct\nb = (8..12000).find { |b| n.digits(b) == [7, 7, 7] }\n\nputs b ? \"A jackpot in base #{b}\" : \"Not a jackpot\"",
